msContents.summary: Commentary on Birjandī's Bīst bāb dar taqvīm, a short treatise on chronology and the computation of almanacs; some tables have been ruled, but left unfilled.

author.persName: Gunābādī, Muẓaffar ibn Muḥammad Qāsim, -1621 or 1622

supportDesc.extent: ii, 99, ii leaves : 200 x 108 (155 x 60) mm, bound to 200 x 105 mm

layoutDesc.layout: 21 long lines with marginalia, geometrical shapes and tables.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in rapid nastaʻliq in black ink; pointed.

decoDesc.decoNote: Rubrications in two shades of red; tables and geometrical shapes in red and black.

binding.p: Red leather over pasteboard with faint, blind-tooled frame; stencilled paper doublures with a large, central motif of blue flowers with green leaves and stems on a bright purple ground surrounded by a wide border composed of green vines and edges with blue parallel line in-fill.
